This paper is about deep reinforcement learning algorithms, which are commonly studied in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and systems and control (cs.SY). The paper specifically focuses on combining exploration and exploitation in these algorithms, which is a common theme in these sub-categories. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG, followed by cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.NE, and cs.SY.
